username-recon
==============

This plugin re-implements the username-enumeration technique popularized by the
Sherlock Project. The detection engine (hunt.py) is original, dependency-free
code written for this plugin.

The bundled site manifest (skills/username-search/data/data.json) is derived from
the Sherlock Project's community-maintained site list, which is distributed under
the MIT License.

  Sherlock Project, https://github.com/sherlock-project/sherlock
  Copyright (c) Sherlock Project contributors
  Licensed under the MIT License.

Use `hunt.py update` to refresh the username manifest from the upstream community list.

The email-detection manifest (skills/username-search/data/email_data.json) and the
infostealer-lookup integration are re-implemented in this plugin's own dependency-free
engine, with detection logic (endpoints and markers) derived from the user-scanner
project, which is distributed under the MIT License.

  user-scanner, https://github.com/kaifcodec/user-scanner
  Copyright (c) user-scanner contributors
  Licensed under the MIT License.

The infostealer check queries the Hudson Rock OSINT API; data is provided by Hudson
Rock (https://www.hudsonrock.com) and that lookup is off unless explicitly requested.

This plugin is intended for lawful, authorized use only, such as checking your own
accounts, consented investigations, security research, and brand/impersonation
monitoring. Respect each site's Terms of Service and rate limits.
